I always talk to my clients about the importance of staying connected to both your roots and your wings.

My roots begin in a hospital in the middle of a cult in South Carolina - where in the middle of a scary world that would not accept me for who I was, the doctor who delivered me as a baby was named Dr. Angel.

Even though my childhood was often terrifying and painful, I held onto the truth that I was supposed to be here - that it was not all a big mistake.

It helped to think about the fact that a literal “angel” had dropped me off on earth. 💜

I’ve felt loving support in the invisible realm ever since - continually guiding me, helping me, protecting me, and blessing me.

I know unconditional love has been there for me all along, and I am so thankful. 

That brings me to my wings. 

As I look forward to the future, I know that I’m just getting started - with so much more still to create!

I don’t know all the forms it will take.

I do know that I’m very passionate about bringing people together for extraordinary experiences they never forget. 

So on the night of my ‘22 First Noelle Ball, I stood at the center of my power with a beautiful look that @thestylistwitch created for me called “Angel Baby.” 

Baby sky blue/white church loafers 
for little Stephen 
and golden luxury wings 
for where we’re headed.
Roots and wings. 

All things are possible for the one who believes.

This has always been the message and will always be the message.

Thank you for being part of the story. 

I believe in you and I always will. 

📸: @paul_archuleta

When I started planning the ball for this year, I thought for months about who the right person would be to take us to midnight.

I wanted music that was joyful, soulful, high energy, universal, groovy, fresh but timeless, and unbelievably fun.

Soundcloud suggested a sunrise mix to me from a Brooklyn DJ named N2N one day, and I couldn’t get enough. Everything worked out perfectly for @n2nmusic to be able to join us and mix live at the center of the ball. 

I had to do a post of appreciation because from the brief moment we had backstage to get centered before everything started to the tequila shot that kicked off our night to the final song that crossed the line of midnight …. this year’s ball would not have been the same without you, Nick. Thank you for being you - I’ll say to you what you wrote on that soundcloud mix I found; you’re a superstar. 

And this video of the late night crew dancing behind the booth to September just conveys the energy better than words ever could. 🕺🏽🫶🏼

The Ball You Know, The Story You Don't: 

I wanted to share a WILD story that few people know to inspire & encourage you:

A few weeks ago ... 
With *12 days* between us & the ball - 

Our original venue called to tell us they were cancelling ALL December events for reasons that had nothing to do w/ us. 

It was shocking & infuriating & heartbreaking all at once. 

We had spent 5 months planning the ball at THIS space. 
(nothing else like it)

Visualizing. Building. Planning. 
100s of hours of work.

Then we get the news. 

Right then, I knew I had a choice as to how I would respond to a moment that felt unimaginable.

More than anything else, I was committed to myself and to you all: 
WE ARE GOING TO THE BALL. 

I told my team, 
whether we create a miracle w/ this venue
or a miracle somewhere new ... 

We are making this happen. 

All things are possible for the one who believes - esp when you have an incredible team believing w/ you. 

I remembered a venue I had previously thought, “We might be ready to take the ball here in 2 or 3 years.”

LOL, life sped up the timeline. 

On Dec. 8th,
I stood there in our brand new venue 
that somehow felt absolutely perfect 
and welcomed you all to the ball. 

The vast majority of you had no idea how much it meant to me to be in that moment, & I didn’t need you to. 

But I wanted to tell you now 
just how much of a miracle that really was. 

I found out later:
a major influencer brand
also got cancelled on by the venue -
& they just canned their event altogether. 
They didn't think it was worth trying to pull it off in time. 

Well … I thought the ball was worth it.

That those moments w/ our community under the sparkling lights were worth it. 

Too significant & special & meaningful 
not to do everything in our power to make it happen.

Thank you for being part of the miracle.

I appreciate that it means the world to so many of you to be there.
May it inspire you to keep creating & believing w/ your own dreams.

Now you know how committed I am to where this is headed.

If we had to build a brand new event in 12 days
& that is STILL how it leaped forward 
from year 1 to 2 ….

Just imagine where we’re going next. 😉

met gala meets reality tv meets adult prom ✨

from an elegant slow dance 
to wild late night moves, 
the ball has it ALL. 🥇🎄🪩

and we’re already ready to do it all over again!

thank you @geo.vany for your cinematic magic ✨

YOU, risking absolutely everything for your dream ... 

I see you. 

YOU, moving forward even though nobody else around you understands and it doesn't make any logical sense ... 

I see you. 

YOU, saying another goodbye because someone or something simply doesn't belong in your life anymore 

I see you. 

YOU, investing yet again though people in your life are telling you to give up on the idea & stop wasting money

I see you. 

YOU, putting one foot in front of the other even though you don't entirely know where it's all leading -

I see you. 

I know what it's like to walk by faith. 

I know that walking by faith and not by sight *sounds* a whole lot sexier
than it *feels* when you're actually living it. 

I know how overwhelming it can be
to feel like you have to shed yet another layer
and step into a whole new version of yourself
to become the person you're really called to be. 

This has been my journey for the past 9 years. 

This is still the journey I'm on today.

Today more than ever. 

Because this is really just the beginning for me ... 

Life is changing a lot for me right now.

In big and bold and beautiful ways. 

Sometimes it's exciting.

Sometimes it's disorienting. 

Sometimes both. 😅

But I love and show up for myself through it all. 

And one thing I've noticed? 

It's the absolute hardest when I refuse to let myself be supported.

That I know for sure.

There is always so much support available for me. 

Support is one person, decision, investment, message away at all times. 

Let's keep moving forward together, family. 

Your life matters. 

Your message matters. 

Your work matters. 

I know that you feel it. 

You're going to make it.

You're going to be okay. 

You're going to live every single bit of your destiny here. 

Breathe in and let God hug you right now. 

It is safe for you to go to the next level.

It is safe for you to shine at your absolute brightest.

It is safe for you to be 100% ALL OF YOU RIGHT NOW. 

I love you more than words can express.

xo stephen

When I was taking public speaking in high school, 
my teacher would always tell me,
“Stop being so preachy. This isn’t church.” 🤣😅

I couldn’t help it.
It’s who I am.
When I believe in something,
I speak with passion. 🔥🎤

When I met the very first life coach to ever be in my life, I remember sharing with him my inner conflict about this idea. 

I had recently left the megachurch world.
I wasn’t going to start a church or work in a church.
I still had judgment on the idea of coming across “preachy.” 

And I will never forget what he said to me:

“The problem wasn’t the preaching.
The problem was the guilt and fear and shame.

Your message is so rooted in love.
And the world needs it.

You should 100% own it and preach your heart out” 🥹

This new IG page is where my teaching is primarily going to go. 

If you resonate and want spiritual teaching full of faith, metaphysics, and unconditional love, welcome! 🤗

I believe in you and I always will.

xo stephen

I don’t think I’ve ever shared something more impactful than the series I’m teaching through right now -> 
77 Days Of Goodness ✨

After almost a decade of doing this work as a coach, it’s so clear to me that many people are pursuing goals & dreams, while subconsciously believing that they don’t get to have them, that they’re not worthy/deserving/ready, or even that God might get upset at them for asking for so much. 

And it’s the most counterproductive, not to mention frustrating, thing in the world to be hustling hard for something you want while maintaining an inner belief system that blocks you at every turn. 

This series is the answer to that in consciousness - upgrading your identity and belief system permanently, one idea at a time.

If I could give one gift to every person on earth, it would be knowing and receiving these truths for themselves, as that truly changes everything. 💜

And the incredible results, miracles, and personal stories people have been sharing with me so far on this journey confirm it 🤗

I know many people are going through immense personal challenges right now, and I certainly know the world feels heavy and scary in many ways right now. I am not minimizing any of that or denying any of that. 

But in a time that might feel dark to you, it might be just what you need to fill your heart with some gentle, life-changing, healing truths that speak to the deepest part of who you are. 

Join me for 77 Days of Goodness now - and see how it changes your life before the end of the year. 

You can tune in on YouTube or The Stephen Lovegrove Show on Apple podcasts 🙏🏼

I believe in you and I always will.

xo stephen

3 moments I want to share to help you understand the significance of this photo: 

Moment 1: Last year, I found myself speaking into a microphone over a noisy room - pushing past the sound of dozens of people chatting loudly while I tried to share a message on my heart & felt unheard.

Clarity depends on contrast - sometimes we have to live through an experience to discover what we actually want instead.

I soon realized I had outgrown something I had created in the past. 

It was a sign to pivot, to transition, to create something new that was in alignment with who I am now. 

Moment 2: I did an exercise that I felt intuitively guided to do (and one that I’d invite you to do) 

I asked myself, what would I want to do every single day? What would my ideal "every day" be?

(Note: let your desires & dreams evolve over time!)

When I did this exercise, a clear answer emerged: I was ready to be speaking in person again to aligned audiences w/ a message from my heart. 

I hadn't realized I missed it so much - but as I looked back, it suddenly became clear - these moments were often my very best memories. 

Moment 3: As I stepped into using my voice as a spiritual leader more than ever, I found myself getting discouraging news. 

That there was something seriously wrong w/ my throat, & I’d be needing vocal surgery plus a total vocal rest & recovery period.

I particularly wanted to share this moment bc as you pursue any vision in life, there will be moments where it feels like nothing is working, nothing is changing, & threats & problems are popping up everywhere.

It is crucial in those moments that you continue. 

That you not interpret them as signs you don't get to have what you want.
